description: As Vice President Kamala Harris faces continued pressure from progressives over U.S. military aid to Israel, some Republicans see an opportunity to win over Jewish voters in key swing states.
title: As war in Gaza fractures Democrats, Republicans see an opening with Jewish voters

description: JPMorgan Chase is filing lawsuits against customers who exploited a viral technical glitch this summer that allowed people to pull huge amounts from Chase ATMs.
title: JP Morgan Chase is suing customers over 'infinite money glitch' ATM scam

description: An Israeli airstrike on a building in northern Gaza overnight killed at least 60 Palestinians, according to Gaza's Health Ministry.
title: An Israeli airstrike in north Gaza killed dozens of people, as parliament bans UNRWA

description: Nadra Wilson and other Virginians got letters saying her U.S. citizenship was in question, along with her voter registration. “I was born in Brooklyn, N.Y. — I'm a citizen,” Wilson told NPR.
title: U.S. citizens are among the voters removed in Virginia’s controversial purge

description: Garr's breakout role was as sexy Inga in Young Frankenstein. She earned an Oscar nomination for her role in the 1982 film Tootsie, and played Phoebe's mom on the sitcom Friends.
title: Teri Garr, actor, comedian and multiple sclerosis ambassador, dies at 79

description: Former Trump adviser Steve Bannon was back to hosting his daily podcast "War Room" just hours after his release from federal prison.
title: Steve Bannon says feels 'empowered' after four months in federal prison

description: The Republican nominee's remarks come days after jokes about Puerto Ricans at his New York rally prompted backlash.

description: Two politically pointed statues have mysteriously appeared in the nation’s capital in the leadup to the election: a pile of poop on the former House speaker's desk and a hand holding a tiki torch.
title: Poop on Pelosi's desk, a neo-Nazi tiki torch: Mysterious statues are popping up in D.C.

description: The cleric takes over after Israel killed Hezbollah's longtime leader, Hassan Nasrallah, in an airstrike in a Beirut suburb in late September.
title: Hezbollah picks cleric Naim Kassem to lead the Lebanese militant group

description: Trump’s rally speeches have become increasingly erratic in the final days of his campaign. And, Israel has voted to ban the United Nations aid agency in Gaza.
title: How Trump’s speeches have changed. And, Israel threatens to ban aid agency in Gaza

description: Here's a costume that won't take a lot of fuss — and will earn you the title "world's scariest animal" this Halloween.
title: This DIY Halloween costume turns you into the world's scariest animal

description: In the rural, red parts of Pennsylvania, young Democratic organizers have a plan to lose by less to win the state for Vice President Harris. But former President Donald Trump's campaign isn't worried.
title: Colleges are key to Democrats' strategy to lose by less in rural Pennsylvania

description: A Biden administration rule allows people in the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals program to enroll in ACA health plans and qualify for subsidies. Nineteen states are seeking to block the rule.
title: 'Dreamers' can get Obamacare this year, unless a court case stops them

description: For 50 years, a secretive group of government workers has been preparing for the worst. Here's a rare look inside the team that's ready to respond to a nuclear incident anywhere, anytime.
title: Meet America's secret team of nuclear first responders

description: Vice President Harris and Trump's former chief of staff say Trump fits the definition of "fascist." Scholars who agree say the term is useful as a distress signal for the threat to democracy.
title: Harris called Trump a 'fascist.' Experts debate what fascism is -- and isn't

description: A week before Election Day, Vice President Harris will use the backdrop to lay out the case for turning the page on the divisive and chaotic politics of her Republican opponent.
title: Harris returns to the site of Trump’s Jan. 6 rally to make her closing argument

description: Trump fell out with Gov. Brian Kemp after 2020, when Kemp rebuffed his efforts to overturn Georgia’s election result. Their relationship could matter to some voters in a state Trump narrowly lost.
title: In a razor-thin race, Trump's complicated ties with Georgia's governor could matter

description: Geitaoui Hospital has Lebanon's only unit specializing in burn treatment. Since Israel launched an air and ground invasion of the country to fight Hezbollah, burn cases have mounted.

description: A new NAACP survey offers a mixed picture for the vice president. She has gained ground among Black men since August, but about one in five say they are still backing former President Donald Trump.
title: New polling finds Harris gaining with a group she has struggled with: Black men

description: The name Belle da Costa Greene might not ring a bell, but New York's renowned historic Morgan Library and Museum is trying to change that.
title: The true story of a famed librarian and the secret she guarded closely

description: Known for their energy and bombast, Donald Trump’s rally speeches have become increasingly erratic. The former president is visibly tired amid a whirlwind schedule in the final days of the campaign.
title: What are Trump’s final rally speeches like? Lower energy, less focused and running late

description: Don't be surprised if you see fewer chocolate treats in your trick-or-treating loot. Customers are souring on costly chocolate, resulting from a few disappointing cocoa crop years.
title: Why you’re seeing scary-high chocolate candy prices this Halloween

description: The laws do not immediately take effect, but Israel’s international allies said they were deeply worried about their potential impact on Palestinians as the Gaza war’s humanitarian toll worsens.
title: Israel passes laws that may threaten the work of a U.N. aid agency in Gaza

description: Tuttle also recently injured a ligament in his elbow that he said he never fully recovered from. Last week, N.C. State quarterback Grayson McCall said he is retiring due to injuries.
title: University of Michigan quarterback Jack Tuttle is retiring after his 5th concussion
